HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 316
BY REPRESENTATIVES WYBLE AND CHASSION
A RESOLUTION
To urge and request the LSU AgCenter, in coordination with the Southern Ag Center and
the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry, to study and develop
strategies to strengthen small and mid-scale agricultural production and to expand
opportunities for young adults to participate in and pursue careers in agriculture.
WHEREAS, agriculture is a vital component of Louisiana's economy, culture, and
rural communities and is directly tied to workforce development, economic growth,
employment opportunities, long-term food security, and the overall stability of the state; and
WHEREAS, small and mid-scale farms that are generally under two hundred fifty
acres are critical to local food systems, rural development, and direct-to-consumer markets;
and
WHEREAS, supporting the continued viability and expansion of such agricultural
operations is essential to sustaining and strengthening local food systems in the state; and
WHEREAS, there are barriers to entry, particularly for individuals under forty years
old, that limit participation in agriculture and hinder growth in agricultural production; and
WHEREAS, addressing these challenges requires attention to infrastructure, training,
and market access, which producers have identified as key needs for agricultural operations.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the LSU AgCenter, in coordination
with the Southern Ag Center and the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and Forestry, to
study and develop strategies or best practices, including those from other states, to expand
production on farms under two hundred fifty acres, increase entry into agriculture among
young adults, and strengthen direct-to-consumer and value-added agricultural markets.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the study shall include but not be limited to the
following areas:
(1) Sales and marketing training for direct-to-consumer producers.
(2) Access to processing facilities, particularly for poultry and small livestock.
